B026C040V001	26	40	1	In the five and twentieth year of our captivity, in the 
B026C040V002	26	40	2	Into the lande of Israel brought he me by a diuine vision, & set me vpon a very hie mountaine, whereupon was as the building of a citie, toward the South.
B026C040V003	26	40	3	And he brought me there, and, behold, [there was] a 
B026C040V004	26	40	4	And the man said vnto me, Sonne of man, beholde with thine eyes, and heare with thine eares, and set thine heart vpon all that I shal shew thee: for to the intent, that they might be shewed thee, art thou brought hither: declare al that thou seest, vnto the house of Israel.
B026C040V005	26	40	5	And beholde, I sawe a wall on the outside of the house round about: and in the mans hand was a reede to measure with, of sixe cubites long, by the cubite, and an hand breadth: so he measured the breadth of the buylding with one reede, and the height with one reede.
B026C040V006	26	40	6	Then came he vnto the gate, which looketh towarde the East, and went vp the stayres thereof, and measured the poste of the gate, which was one reede broade, and the other poste of the gate, which was one reede broade.
B026C040V007	26	40	7	And euery chamber was one reede long, & one reede broad, & betweene the chambers were fiue cubites: & the post of the gate by the porch of the gate within was one reede.
B026C040V008	26	40	8	He measured also the porche of the gate within with one reede.
B026C040V009	26	40	9	Then measured he the porch of the gate of eight cubites, and the postes thereof, of two cubites, and the porch of the gate was inward.
B026C040V010	26	40	10	And the chambers of the gate Eastwarde, were three on this side, and three on that side: they three were of one measure, and the postes had one measure on this side, and one on that side.
B026C040V011	26	40	11	And he measured the breadth of the entrie of the gate ten cubites, and the height of the gate thirteene cubites.
B026C040V012	26	40	12	The space also before the chambers was one cubite on this side, and the space was one cubite on that side, and the chambers were sixe cubites on this side and sixe cubites on that side.
B026C040V013	26	40	13	He measured then the gate from the roufe of a chamber to the toppe of the gate: the breadth was fiue and twentie cubites, doore against doore.
B026C040V014	26	40	14	He made also postes of threescore cubites, and the postes of the court, and of the gate had one measure round about.
B026C040V015	26	40	15	And vpon the forefront of the entry of the gate vnto the forefront of the porch of the gate within were fiftie cubites.
B026C040V016	26	40	16	And there were narrowe windowes in the chambers, & in their postes within the gate round about, and likewise to the arches: and the windowes went rounde about within: and vpon the postes were palme trees.
B026C040V017	26	40	17	Then brought he me into the outwarde court, and lo, there were chambers, & a pauement made for the court round about, & thirtie chambers were vpon the pauement.
B026C040V018	26	40	18	And the pauement was by the side of the gates ouer against the length of the gates, and the pauement was beneath.
B026C040V019	26	40	19	Then hee measured the breadth from the forefront of the lower gate without, vnto the forefront of the court within, an hundreth cubits Eastward and Northward.
B026C040V020	26	40	20	And the gate of the outwarde court, that looked toward the North, measured he after the length and breadth thereof.
B026C040V021	26	40	21	And the chambers thereof were, three on this side, and three on that side, and the postes thereof and the arches thereof were after the measure of the first gate: the length thereof was fiftie cubites, and the breadth fiue and twentie cubites.
B026C040V022	26	40	22	And their windowes, and their arches with their palme trees, were after the measure of the gate that looketh toward the East, and the going vp vnto it had seuen steppes, and the arches therof were before them.
B026C040V023	26	40	23	And the gate of the inner court stoode ouer against the gate towarde the North, and towarde the East, and hee measured from gate to gate an hundreth cubites.
B026C040V024	26	40	24	After that, he brought mee towarde the South, and loe, there was a gate towarde the South, and hee measured the postes thereof, and the arches thereof according to these measures.
B026C040V025	26	40	25	And there were windowes in it, and in the arches thereof round about, like those windowes: the height was fiftie cubites, and the breadth fiue and twentie cubites.
B026C040V026	26	40	26	And there were seuen steps to go vp to it, and the arches thereof were before them: and it had palme trees, one on this side, and another on that side vpon the post thereof.
B026C040V027	26	40	27	And there was a gate in the inner court towarde the South, and he measured from gate to gate towarde the South an hundreth cubites.
B026C040V028	26	40	28	And he brought me into the inner court by the South gate, and he measured the South gate according to these measures,
B026C040V029	26	40	29	And the chambers thereof, and the postes thereof, and the arches thereof according to these measures, and there were windowes in it, and in the arches thereof rounde about, it was fiftie cubites long and fiue and twentie cubites broade.
B026C040V030	26	40	30	And the arches round about were fiue and twenty cubites long, and fiue cubites broad.
B026C040V031	26	40	31	And the arches thereof were towarde the vtter court, and palme trees were vpon the postes thereof, and the going vp to it had eight steppes.
