B026C042V004	26	42	4	And before the chambers was a gallery of ten cubites wide, and within was a way of one cubite, and their doores towarde the North.
B026C042V005	26	42	5	Nowe the chambers aboue were narower: for those chambers seemed to eate vp these, to wit, the lower, and those that were in the middes of the building.
